1. Definitions. 
1.1. "Core(s)" means a physical core that is a processing unit within a 
processor. When running on a virtual machine, Core means a virtual core. 
1.2. "Enterprise Edition" means the version of the Software designated as
the Enterprise Edition of the Software on this Order. Form. 
1.3. "Enterprise Period" means the term designated in this Order Form for any 
Enterprise Edition Software being ordered under this Order Form. 
1.4.  "Evaluation Edition" means the version of the Software designated as the 
Evaluation Edition of the Software on this Order Form. 
1.5.  "Evaluation Period" means the period commencing on the Effective Date and
ending on the date that is forty-five (45) days thereafter or as extended by 
Clustrix in writing. 
1.6. "Professional Edition" means the version of the Software designated as the
Professional Edition of the Software on this Order Form. "Professional Period" 
means the term designated in this Order Form for any Professional Edition 
Software being ordered under this Order Form. 
1.7. "Product" means the Software and all associated documentation (if any) 
("Documentation") 
1.8. "Software" means Clustrix’s proprietary software application provided 
hereunder.

